This paper is about improving the accuracy of a dependency parser using a training-with-exploration procedure. This topic falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses modifications needed for a probabilistic neural network, which suggests that it may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions parsing accuracies for both English and Chinese, indicating that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
